#Adhoc commands is basically simple linux one time usage commands
adhoc commands start with 1="ansible" keyword 2="group name" 3=argument "mean execute the inverted comma commands" 

for example:
ansible linux_servers -a "ls" #linux_servers is the group name which contain ip addresses of the servers
ansible linux_servers -a "touch file1"
ansible linux_servers -a "sudo apt-get install python3"
ansible linux_servers -a "sudo apt-get install apache2" 

Important to NOTE
In adhoc commands there is no idempotency.

